Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan will play their sixth match of the 2023 World Cup against South Africa at the MA Chidambaram Stadium in Chennai on 27 October.
South Africa have won three of their four matches so far, by margins of 102 runs, 134 runs and 229 runs against Sri Lanka, Australia and England respectively.
Pakistan's batting has been largely consistent, but their bowling has been a bit of a letdown.
South Africa's batters have been in belligerent form, scoring 300+ in every one of their full innings so far.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will begin at 2:00pm IST.
The two nations have faced each other 82 times in ODIs, with South Africa winning 51 times and Pakistan winning 30 times.
